*********************** VARIAN NMR USER GROUP LIBRARY ***********************
                              NEW MANUAL ENTRY

Syntax:		makestud(width, pulselength)

Description:	Makes sech-amplitude/tanh-frequency swept decoupling with
		250 steps, any bandwidth, and any pulselength. The output is
		a file in the local shapelib named st_width_pulselength.DEC,
		e.g., st_2_1o2.DEC, where 1o2 means 1.2ms.  This macro loads
		the name of the decoupling file into dseq, sets dres=1.0, and
		calculates dmf.  The number of steps can be increased by
		changing 250 and 249 everywhere they occur in the macro.
		References: Starcuk et al, JMR, A107, 24 (1994)
			    Bendall, JMR, A112, 126 (1995)

Arguments:	width - decoupling bandwidth in KHz
		pulselength - 180 degrees pulse length in milliseconds

Examples:	makestud(2,1.2)
